n the\nmain-sequence and starburst modes, respectively. Because we have not introduced\nempirical corrections to enhance these estimates, in principle, our method\nshould be applicable to lower luminosity galaxies. This will enable use of the\n21 micron band of the Mid-Infrared Instrument (MIRI) on board the JWST to\nprovide an extremely sensitive tracer of obscured SFR in individual\nstar-forming galaxies across the peak of the cosmic star formation history.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Jul 2011 20:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 4 Sep 2011 06:36:19 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 22 Feb 2013 03:05:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
